member.example:
This sample shows how to call GetAsync with required parameters and parse the result.

var credential = new DefaultAzureCredential();
var client = new MeasurementClassificationClient(credential);

Response response = await client.GetAsync("<measurementId>", "<schemaName>");

JsonElement result = JsonDocument.Parse(response.ContentStream).RootElement;
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("schemaName").ToString());
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("classificationObject").ToString());
Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("etag").ToString());

member.remarks:
Below is the JSON schema for the response payload.
Response Body:
Schema for MeasurementClassification: { schemaName: string, # Required. classificationObject: string, # Required. etag: string, # Required. }

