member.example:
This sample shows how to call ListAsync with required parameters and parse the result.

var credential = new DefaultAzureCredential();
var client = new MeasurementClassificationClient(credential);

await foreach (var data in client.ListAsync("<measurementId>"))
{
    JsonElement result = JsonDocument.Parse(data.ToStream()).RootElement;
    Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("schemaName").ToString());
    Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("classificationObject").ToString());
    Console.WriteLine(result.GetProperty("etag").ToString());
}

member.remarks:
Below is the JSON schema for one item in the pageable response.
Response Body:
Schema for Array: { schemaName: string, # Required. classificationObject: string, # Required. etag: string, # Required. }

